# Types colocation (`types.ts`)

Detail for [app-module-structure.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/app-module-structure.mdc): **`interface` / `type` / `enum` in `types.ts`** same folder as module (not beside main class file).

## Rule

In module folder (e.g. `backend/apps/search-service/src/app/search/`):

- File exports **`export class`** (main service/class) → no exported `type` / `interface` / `enum` in same file.
- Put in **`types.ts` in that directory** (default: one `types.ts` per folder; not `foo.types.ts` unless repo exception exists).

In class file:

```typescript
import type { SomeType, ISomeParams } from './types';
```

Barrels: re-export from `index.ts` only when folder already uses barrel pattern in same app.

## Exceptions

- **`*.spec.ts` / `*.test.ts`:** local fixture/helper types OK in test file; no move to module `types.ts`.
- **`.tsx`:** glob is `*.ts` only; component props separate from "class + types" split.

## Bad / good

```typescript
// BAD — types next to class in one file
export type Status = 'a' | 'b';
export interface Params { x: number; }
export class Service { }

// GOOD — types.ts
export type Status = 'a' | 'b';
export interface Params { x: number; }

// GOOD — service.ts
import type { Params, Status } from './types';
export class Service { }
```
